  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\n<!-- Is your feature request related to a specific problem? Is it just a crazy idea? Tell us about it! -->\r\nI simply wonder if when the internal `_burn` function on `ERC20` is called, if it should increase the balance of the `address(0)` in the `_balances` mapping.\r\n\r\nCurrently, this is not done by default. I just wondered if this should be the default behaviour in ERC20, or if this should be an implementation detail.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/9e8b74a0e2c8a6e87f7fa88318f15017d4b14524/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol#L277-L293\r\n\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n<!-- Please describe your feature request in detail. -->\r\n\r\nFor instance, I have noticed on Etherscan that:\r\n- for the DAI token contract, the `address(0)` has some balance.\r\n\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/token/0x6b175474e89094c44da98b954eedeac495271d0f#readContract\r\n<img width=\"316\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31145285/236240423-498e0a0a-47ed-4340-abec-e99934735f9e.png\">\r\n\r\n- for the USDC token contract, the `address(0)` has no balance.\r\n\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/token/0xa0b86991c6218b36c1d19d4a2e9eb0ce3606eb48#readProxyContract\r\n<img width=\"383\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31145285/236240358-f8841021-f342-4212-bcfc-5c4aaefa441e.png\">\r\n\r\n> Although I have no idea if this is the normal behaviour or if this is intended in each implementation.\r\n\r\n@Amxx @frangio ",
